<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOVIES TO TAPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Forbidden Planet (Channel 5 Sunday at 10 a.m.): Celebrated 1956 sci-fi version 
of Shakespeare's "The Tempest" starring Walter Pidgeon and Anne Francis. (2:00) 
</P>
<P>
The Evil Mind (Channel 11 Monday at 10 a.m.): Sounds intriguing: Claude Rains 
plays a phony mind-reader whose predictions start coming true. Made in England 
in 1934 as "The Clairvoyant." (2:00) 
</P>
<P>
Lucky Luciano (TMC Tuesday at 2 p.m.): Francesco Rosi's engrossing 1973 
English-language production, with the Italian director's characteristic 
convoluted structuring, expansive scope and easy elegance of style -- and with 
Gian Maria Volonte in the title role. (2:00) 
</P>
<P>
The Spider's Stratagem (Z Friday at 9:30 a.m.): In this stunning, ambitious 
1970 adaptation of a Jorge Luis Borges story, Bernardo Bertolucci tells of a 
man (Giulio Brogi) caught up in a tantalizing quest for the truth about the 
death of his father, an anti-fascist martyr. (2:00) 
</P>
<P>
Before the Revolution (Z Saturday at 3 p.m.): Bertolucci took his inspiration 
from Stendhal's "The Charterhouse of Parma" for his rich and astonishing 1964 
film about youth and politics. (2:00) 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Motion Picture Review 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA012289-0004 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 8404 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
January 22, 1989, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
