IT MUST BE England's chilly climate that inspires so many handsomely designed 
sweaters. Duckworth uses all-over patterns (flowers, peacocks, ducks), lots of 
colors -- and tiny needles. But the book is more than a series of instructions; 
each chapter is introduced with a very pretty arrangement, and in the back of 
