<P>
HERE'S A SUITABLE topic for a psychologist: Why do so many people who have no 
intention (or at least an extremely remote possibility) of ever building a home 
find immense pleasure in looking at house plans? Those small blueprints, with 
accompanying drawings of stately entrances to single-story cottages, gargantuan 
estates or vacation hideaways, are irresistible to some of us. This hefty 
paperback volume offers 360 floor plans, including farmhouses and 
plantation-style mansions. Decisions, decisions. ($8.95) Judith Sims 
