<HEADLINE>
<P>
CLOSING QUOTE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"We weren't trying to be heroes or anything, but they were threatening to cut 
us off. Setting our own prices is part of our business philosophy." 
</P>
<P>
 -- Charles Bain, a spokesman for Service Merchandise Co., the retailer 
credited with blowing the whistle on what prosecutors called a major illegal 
pricing scheme by home electronics giant Panasonic Co. 
</P>
</TEXT>
