<HEADLINE>
<P>
ALL ABOUT TRAVEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In Jerry Hulse's Travel Tips (Dec. 4) there was a recommendation for 
"personalized itineraries" under the heading of "Tailored Itineraries." What 
caused us to take notice was the assertion that "travel agents are skilled at 
obtaining bargain fares," but it is necessary to go to a consultant who is not 
an agent for expert itinerary planning. 
</P>
<P>
We at Newport Travel Concepts pride ourselves on providing our clients with the 
most up-to-date faring and routing expertise and thoroughly researched and 
personalized itineraries. We have created specialized trips throughout the 
globe, including Africa, Asia and literally around the world. We provide 
service with respect to every aspect of travel and believe that your readers 
should know that there are travel agents who "do it all." 
</P>
<P>
FLORENCE FELDMAN 
</P>
<P>
TISH HILBERT 
</P>
<P>
JACKIE MANION 
</P>
<P>
JODY VAUGHAN 
</P>
