<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIRST SPRING GAMES SCHEDULED FOR MARCH 2 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Only six weeks and counting . . . the Boston Red Sox and Chicago White Sox open 
the spring training season March 2 in Sarasota, Fla., and every other team 
except Cleveland plays the next day. 
</P>
<P>
Atlanta faces Georgia Tech in another game March 2. The World Series champion 
Dodgers start the next day against Kansas City. 
</P>
<P>
The Grapefruit and Cactus Leagues run through April 2, the day before the 
regular season begins. 
</P>
</TEXT>
