<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WORLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Syrian Defense Minister Mustafa Talas alleged that Israel duped an American 
soldier into carrying the bomb that blew up a Pan Am jetliner over Scotland on 
Dec. 21, killing 270 people. "An agent of Israeli intelligence, Mossad, handed 
him the bomb-laden bag to carry in return for $300,000, claiming it was 
diamonds worth $500,000 needed to be smuggled into the United States," Talas 
said in an interview published in Kuwait's daily Al-Qabas. British 
investigators determined the plane was destroyed by a bomb placed in the 
luggage hold, but they have not said who was responsible. In Israel, a Foreign 
Ministry spokesman called Talas' allegation "ridiculous and malicious." 
</P>
</TEXT>
