<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE STATE; 
</P>
<P>
200 ABORTION FOES ARRESTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
About 200 people were arrested at an anti-abortion demonstration in Northern 
California marking the 16th anniversary of the U.S. Supreme Court decision 
legalizing abortion. Hundreds of other anti-abortion activists staged peaceful 
rallies in Los Angeles and San Bernardino counties. The arrests wewre made when 
a crowd of about 400 protesters in Sunnyvale attempted to block entry to a 
family planning clinic, police said. The demonstration, held by Bay Area 
Rescue, a local coalition of anti-abortion groups, also drew about 150 
supporters of Roe vs. Wade, the landmark 1973 Supreme Court decision. 
</P>
</TEXT>
