<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE STATE; 
</P>
<P>
RECALL ISSUED FOR ICE CREAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Stater Brothers market chain recalled some of its house-brand ice cream 
because of possible exposure to ammonia from a refrigerant leak during 
manufacture. Staters spokesman Tom Reingrover said the half-gallon packages 
affected contain golden vanilla and chocolate ice cream and are marked with the 
code number 092289. "It's strictly a precautionary thing," he said. "We found 
very little product affected." Reingrover said it was not immediately 
determined which of the chain's 101 markets in Southern California received the 
ice cream. 
</P>
</TEXT>
