<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPORTS ET CETERA: SDSU WOMEN COME BACK TO BEAT UNLV 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chana Perry scored 17 points, Julie Evans added 12 and Crystal Lee had 10 
assists as the San Diego State University women's basketball team came back to 
defeat host Nevada Las Vegas, 55-51, in a nonconference game between national 
powers. 
</P>
<P>
SDSU (15-1) is ranked No. 12 but coming off a 99-80 loss Thursday to Long 
Beach. UNLV, ranked 19th, led at halftime, 28-26. 
</P>
<P>
Lee made both ends of a 1-and-1 with 7 seconds to play to ice the victory for 
SDSU. 
</P>
<P>
Pauline Jordan scored a game-high 19 points for UNLV (15-2). 
</P>
<P>
UC San Diego was outshot from the field but made 6 of 15 3-point attempts and 
defeated Colby (Maine) College, 81-72, to advance to the championship of the 
Smith College National Invitational Tournament in Northampton, Mass. 
</P>
<P>
Tracy Ragatz, who was 5 of 10 from 3-point range, led UCSD (11-4) with 27 
points. Beth Koenig, 9 of 10 from the free throw line, had 20 points and Jill 
Koster added 18 points and 10 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
Kim Derrington scored 24 for Colby. 
</P>
<P>
In today's championship game, UCSD plays host Smith College, which defeated 
Trinity College (San Antonio, Tex.), 58-46. 
</P>
<P>
Candida Echeverria scored 14 points, Rochelle Lightner 12 and Julie Lemery 10 
as the University of San Diego defeated Santa Clara, 69-60, in a West Coast 
Athletic Conference game. 
</P>
<P>
USD is 6-8 and 2-2. Jennifer Lucas scored a game-high 19 for Santa Clara (5-13, 
1-3). 
</P>
<P>
Fresno Pacific outrebounded host Point Loma Nazarene, 45-28, and made 21 of 26 
free throws (81%) en route to a 78-54 Golden State Athletic Conference victory. 
</P>
<P>
Camille Armijo led Point Loma Nazarene (11-8, 1-2) with 18 points, Shelly 
Stokes had 12 and Shannon Anderson added 10. 
</P>
<P>
Kellie Fry scored a game-high 19 for Fresno Pacific (12-4, 4-0). Robin Turner 
and Irene Robles added 12 each, and Cindy Seymore had 11. 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
Point Loma Nazarene didn't take its first lead until 1:05 remained but then 
hung on for a 79-77 victory over visiting Fresno Pacific in a Golden State 
Athletic Conference game. 
</P>
<P>
Mark Ryan made two free throws with 1:05 to play to put Point Loma Nazarene 
ahead, 75-74, Shawn Stroud made two with 16 seconds to play to make it 77-74, 
and then Stroud hit two more with 11 seconds remaining to give Point Loma 
Nazarene some breathing room. 
</P>
<P>
Ryan led Point Loma Nazarene (5-12, 3-1) with 21 points, Brian Thurston added 
20, and Mark Bulgin and Stroud each had 12. 
</P>
<P>
Donnie Johnson scored 23 points for Fresno Pacific (12-6, 3-1). 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Northridge handed UC San Diego its fourth consecutive loss, 15-8, 
15-8, 12-15, 15-9, in a nonconference match. Jeff Babcock had 14 kills and Nate 
Brown 11 for UCSD (0-4). 
</P>
</TEXT>
