<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMEN'S BASKETBALL; 
</P>
<P>
LONG BEACH TOO MUCH FOR TITANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Cal State Long Beach women's basketball team, taking advantage of 43 
turnovers, defeated Cal State Fullerton, 84-50, Saturday night in a Big West 
Conference game at Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
The Titans committed 28 turnovers in the first half and fell behind, 55-25. 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach, ranked 10th, is 12-4 overall and 6-0 in conference play. Fullerton 
fell to 12-4 and 4-3. 
</P>
<P>
Shameil Coleman was the 49ers' leading scorer for the third straight game, 
getting 15 points. Traci Waites added 13. 
</P>
<P>
Gena Miller, who fouled out with 2:41 left, led Fullerton with 19 points. 
</P>
<P>
UCLA 93, Arizona 69 -- Althea Ford scored 15 points and grabbed 10 rebounds to 
lead the Bruins over the Wildcats in a Pacific 10 game at Westwood. 
</P>
<P>
UCLA (8-7 overall, 4-1 in the Pac-10) led, 42-33, at halftime, then pulled away 
with an 8-0 run early in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
The 93 points set a women's record for the John Wooden Center. The old mark was 
88, set 2 years ago against Arizona State. 
</P>
<P>
Other top scorers for UCLA were Sandra VanEmbricqs with 14, Molly Tideback and 
Rachelle Roulier with 13 apiece and Elaine Youngs with 12. 
</P>
<P>
Arizona (5-11, 0-6) was led by Amy Gamble, who had 19 points and 8 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
UCLA's next game is Friday night at Washington State. 
</P>
<P>
USC 78, Arizona State 58 -- Cherie Nelson scored 30 of her 32 points in the 
second half to lead the Trojans (6-9, 2-3) over the Sun Devils (7-9, 1-5) in a 
Pac-10 game at the North Gym on the USC campus. 
</P>
<P>
Nelson also had 11 rebounds. Other top scorers for USC were Rosalind Hodge with 
14 points and Tammy Story with 13. Karen O'Connor had 20 for Arizona State. 
</P>
