<HEADLINE>
<P>
DAVIS, WILSON LEAD WAVES PAST GONZAGA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SPOKANE, Wash. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pepperdine, behind the scoring of guards Craig Davis and Lamar Wilson, extended 
its winning streak to 4 straight games and remained in a 3-way tie for first 
place in the West Coast Athletic Conference with a 74-70 victory over Gonzaga 
Saturday night before a crowd of 3,700 at the Martin Centre. 
</P>
<P>
The Waves, who have won 17 of 22 from Gonzaga, are 4-0 in the WCAC, as are 
Loyola Marymount and St. Mary's. 
</P>
<P>
Davis, a junior, scored a season-high 26 points on 10-of-15 shooting, including 
6 of 7 from 3-point range. 
</P>
<P>
Wilson, a senior, scored a career-high 15 points. 
</P>
<P>
After a 3-point shot by guard Doug Spradley gave Gonzaga a 47-42 lead with 
14:49 left, the Waves (12-7 overall) scored 16 straight to take a 58-47 lead 
with 9:56 left. Davis scored 11 of the points, including 3 3-pointers. 
</P>
<P>
Gonzaga (10-7, 1-3) made a last run when Spradley, who had a game-high 29 
points, made a 4-point play (he made a 3-pointer and a free throw after being 
fouled on the play). 
</P>
<P>
But Wilson made 2 free throws to give Pepperdine a 70-66 lead. 
</P>
<P>
The Waves made 11 of their last 12 free-throw attempts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
