<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Olympic gold medalist Meldrick Taylor stopped John Wesley Meekins after 7 
rounds at Atlantic City, N.J., to retain the International Boxing Federation 
junior welterweight title. 
</P>
<P>
Meekins (20-2-2), of West Hempstead, N.Y., couldn't answer the bell for the 
eighth round because his right eye was closed, and there was a bad swelling 
under his left eye and a cut over the left eye. 
</P>
<P>
Taylor (21-0-1), of Philadelphia, has won 9 straight fights and has recorded 15 
knockouts in his career. He was cut over the left eye by an accidental head 
butt in the second round, but cut man Ace Marotta kept the gash from becoming a 
factor. 
</P>
