<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
West Germany's Claudia Leistner stepped into the void left by Katarina Witt to 
win the women's gold medal in the European Figure Skating Championships at 
Birmingham, England. 
</P>
<P>
The 23-year-old West German, who also won the school figures and original 
program, was her country's first female titlist since Gundi Busch in 1954. 
</P>
<P>
Natalia Lebedeva of the Soviet Union, at 24 the oldest competitor in the 
women's event, gained the silver. Patricia Neske of West Germany won the 
bronze. 
