<HEADLINE>
<P>
IRVINE'S ORDINANCE ON HUMAN RIGHTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Having read your editorial Jan. 15, I am compelled to write to you. 
</P>
<P>
I find it very disturbing that there are so many otherwise normal people who 
try to excuse the aberration known as homosexuality. 
</P>
<P>
I do not advocate violence toward the poor unfortunates who are trapped in this 
behavior, but I do believe that they should have the decency to keep their 
activities private. Heterosexuals are expected to do as much. The only 
motivation for all the publicity and propaganda favoring homosexuality (and 
there is a great deal of it in movies, television and newspapers) is to snare 
other borderline or unformed individuals into their life style. Have we not 
enough of AIDS and other problems engendered by them without having the media 
producing apologies for them? 
</P>
<P>
Again, I do not care what they do in private. I only ask that they keep their 
activities private and cease proselytizing. 
</P>
<P>
BARBARA G. THOMAS 
</P>
<P>
Garden Grove 
</P>
</TEXT>
