<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
FULLERTON HANDS GAME TO LONG BEACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Cal State Long Beach women's basketball team, taking advantage of 43 
turnovers, defeated Cal State Fullerton, 84-50, in a Big West game Saturday 
night at Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
The Titans had 28 turnovers in the first half while falling behind, 55-25. 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach, ranked 10th in the nation, is 12-4, 6-0 in conference play. 
Fullerton fell to 12-4 and 4-3. 
</P>
<P>
Shameil Coleman was the 49er women's leading scorer for the third consecutive 
game with 15 points. Traci Waites added 13. 
</P>
<P>
Gena Miller, who fouled out with 2:41 left, led Fullerton with 19 points. 
</P>
<P>
In the California Collegiate Athletic Assn.: 
</P>
<P>
Chapman 71, UC Riverside 64 -- Julie King scored 22 points for host Chapman 
(7-9, 2-1). Kim Rieff added 18. Patti Held scored 27 points for Riverside. 
</P>
<P>
In a nonconference game: 
</P>
<P>
The Masters 54, Southern California College 49 -- Laurel Hudgens' two free 
throws in the final second clinched the victory after Southern California 
College's Roxanne Trost made a 3-point basket to cut the margin to three 
points. Gail Brown and Stacey Mounce led Southern California College (4-14) 
with 10 points each. 
</P>
<P>
In women's tennis: 
</P>
<P>
Fresno State 6, Cal State Fullerton 3 -- Fullerton's No. 4 singles player, 
Caroline Sporer, defeated Tara Eden, 4-6, 7-6 (11-9) 6-4, in the Big West 
Conference opener for both teams. Katy McKenzie, at No. 6 singles defeated 
Grace Schreuders, 6-3, 2-6, 6-1. The No. 2 doubles team of Kelli Moore and 
Sporer defeated Fresno State's Valerie Stukovsky and Tara Eden, 6-2, 3-6, 6-3. 
</P>
<P>
In men's swimming: 
</P>
<P>
UC Irvine 169, Cal State Northridge 62 -- The host Anteaters swept the relays, 
winning the 400-meter medley in 3 minutes 35.85 seconds and the 400-meter 
freestyle in 3:11.39, in a nonconference victory in Crawford Hall Pool. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine's Mauro Macchi was a double winner, placing first in the 1,000-meter 
freestyle (10:07.93) and the 500-meter freestyle (4:46.63). Matt Wright won the 
50-meter freestyle (21.96) and the 100-meter freestyle (47.54) for Irvine 
(6-1). 
</P>
<P>
In women's swimming: 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Northridge 140, UC Irvine 93 -- Devon Coate won the 200-meter 
individual medley in 2:13.03 and the 200-meter backstroke in 2:14.13 for Irvine 
(3-5). 
</P>
<P>
In wrestling: 
</P>
<P>
Cleveland State 26, Cal State Fullerton 13 -- The 25th-ranked Titans lost 8 of 
10 matches against No. 26 Cleveland State in a nonconference meet in Ohio. 
Fullerton's David Jones, the No. 5-ranked heavyweight in the nation, pinned 
Cleveland's Heath Mohrman at 1:40. Jones, who leads the team in pins with 7, 
improved his record to 21-3-2. 
</P>
<P>
Erin Millsap also won for the Titans, scoring a technical fall, 21-5, over Mile 
Elsass at 118 pounds. Millsap is 22-4-2. Fullerton is 8-6 in dual meets. 
</P>
