<HEADLINE>
<P>
UNIDENTIFIED MAN DIES OF GUNSHOT WOUND IN SANTA ANA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From a Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An unidentified man died of a gunshot wound early Saturday at Western Medical 
Center in Santa Ana, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The victim, about 25 years old, died at 1:15 a.m. after surgery, Santa Ana 
Police Lt. Hugh Mooney said. Police received a call at 11:32 p.m. Friday of a 
shooting in the 200 block of South Bristol Avenue in Santa Ana. Officers found 
the victim on the sidewalk with a gunshot wound to the upper body. 
</P>
<P>
Mooney said the victim had no identification. The motive for the attack and the 
caliber of weapon used are unknown, Mooney said. 
</P>
<P>
"There is very little to go on," Mooney said. "It's one of those real 
puzzlers." 
</P>
</TEXT>
