<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMEN'S ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
UCLA SETS SCORING MARK IN VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Althea Ford scored 15 points and grabbed 10 rebounds to lead UCLA to a 93-69 
victory over Arizona in a Pacific 10 women's basketball game at UCLA's John 
Wooden Center. 
</P>
<P>
UCLA (8-7, 4-1 in conference play) led only 42-33 at halftime, but pulled away 
with an 8-0 run early in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
The Bruins' 93 points set record for the John Wooden Center. The old mark was 
88, set two years ago against Arizona State. 
</P>
<P>
Other top scorers for UCLA were Sandra VanEmricqs with 14, Molly Tideback and 
Rachelle Roulier with 13 apiece and Elaine Youngs with 12. 
</P>
<P>
Arizona (5-11, 0-6) was led by Amy Gamble, who had 19 points and 8 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
UCLA's next game is Friday at Washington State. 
</P>
<P>
USC 78, Arizona State 58 -- Cherie Nelson scored 30 of her 32 points in the 
second half to lead the Trojans (6-9, 2-3) over the Sun Devils (7-9, 1-5) in a 
Pac-10 game at the North Gym on the USC campus. 
</P>
<P>
Nelson also had 11 rebounds. Other top scorers for USC were Rosalind Hodge with 
14 points and Tammy Story with 13. 
</P>
</TEXT>
